DETAILS: 1452801226U347739DESCRIPTION: New Submission1452801303U347739From: Desai  Vishal  Sent: Thursday  January 14  2016 2:35 PM To: G=MODE SPL Team; G=MODE ETL Team; Pullakandam  Durga; G=MODE Production Support Cc: G=DBA Support MODE Subject: S2C DD_BORROWER SQL  S2C DD_BORROWER SQL is spending most of its time doing full table scan. Based on SQL logic below we are only interested in BORR_ID and ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM from DD_BORROWER. It doesn't look like very active table in terms of DML activity based on MODE_LST_UPDT_DTTM. I think we should create combined index on BORR_ID and ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM and test performance of this SQL in SPL(with PROD volume). With index in place it will do INDEX FAST FULL SCAN on smaller index segment compared to entire table and will improve response time of this SQL.     SELECT /*+ ROWID(DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE) */       TRIM (DD_BORROWER_qry.ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM)           AS ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.AGE_OLDEST_OPEN_TRDL_MO_CNT         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.CR_TRDL_HIGH_CR_AMT         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.MO_SINCE_BNKRT_DISCHARGE_CNT         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.MO_SINCE_FRCLSR_DISCHARGE_CNT         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.OPN_TRDL_CNT         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.CR_TRDL_IN_COLL_AMT         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.MODE_LST_UPDT_DTTM         DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.mode_src_sys_eff_dttm   FROM MDE_PARSED_SVCLOGS.DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE        AS OF SCN SYS_CONTEXT ('Context_AI'  'SCN_VAL')        INNER JOIN        (  SELECT MAX (borr_id) AS borr_id  ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM             FROM MDE_PARSED_SVCLOGS.DD_BORROWER                  AS OF SCN SYS_CONTEXT ('Context_AI'  'SCN_VAL')            WHERE ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM IS NOT NULL         GROUP BY ENTERPRISE_CUSTOMER_NUM) DD_BORROWER_qry           ON DD_BORROWER_qry.borr_id = DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.borr_id        INNER JOIN        (  SELECT MAX (borr_cr_summ_id) AS borr_cr_summ_id  borr_id             FROM MDE_PARSED_SVCLOGS.DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE                  AS OF SCN SYS_CONTEXT ('Context_AI'  'SCN_VAL')            WHERE borr_cr_summ_id IS NOT NULL         GROUP BY borr_id) br_cr           ON br_cr.borr_cr_summ_id =                 DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.borr_cr_summ_id WHERE     DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.mode_lst_updt_dttm <=               TO_TIMESTAMP (SYS_CONTEXT ('Context_AI'  'READY_FOR_USE_DTTM')                              'YYYY/MM/DD HH24:MI:SS.FF')        AND DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.mode_soft_del_ind IS NULL        AND MDE_PARSED_SVCLOGS.DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.ROWID >= :lowrowid        AND MDE_PARSED_SVCLOGS.DD_BORROWER_CREDIT_ATTRIBUTE.ROWID <= :hirowid    Thanks   Vishal Desai Database Analyst  DESCRIPTION: S2C DD_BORROWER SQL  Problem was assigned to ntfymodeplatformsupp as a severity 4 problem.1452801314U347739Problem was assigned to U347739 as a severity 4 problem.1452805162U347739Pending Comments: checking..   Status changed to Pending1453352421AR_ESCALATORSent follow-up date notification to assignee1453402118U347739targeted for R1.16  Pending Comments: targeted for R1.161455750771U347739this is fixed in r116   Status changed to Closed  RESOLUTION: CAUSE GROUP : MODE ETL TEAM & DBA TEAM RESOLUTION : WITH INDEXES IN PLACE IT WILL DO INDEX FAST FULL SCAN ON SMALLER INDEX SEGMENT COMPARED TO ENTIRE TABLE AND WILL IMPROVE RESPONSE TIME OF THIS SQL.

All of Acquisition Credit Risk Management is expecting this SLA to be maintained which agrees to have all transactions processed via our the Decision Engine Services (i.e. GRD  RED  etc.) base on the data specified (per mapping requirements)  and to be parsed and passed down to our analytic repositories every 2 hours accurately. Quality and accurately is our key expectations for this data flowing through this ETL  to avoid repurchases and to help the company stay ahead with regulatory Federal Credit Policies. JOB RUNS SLOW WHICH THREATENS OLAS.  CORE 1 CLEAN UP REQUIRED AT MODE SIDE TO AVOID  MANUAL FILTERING OF CORE 1 DATA ON NIGHTLY RUN . 1432306914X787070Capital Markets Credit Risk (CMCR) technology  also sometimes referred to as Capital Markets Integrated Environment (CMIE) for its DB environment  is a new downstream partner that started receiving data from MODE on 5/16. Since then  we have discovered the main job that sends data to CMIE takes three hours when running sequentially but only 18-30 minutes running in parallel. This change will fix that job so it can be delivered on time to meet OLAs. When it was taking three hours  CMCR missed a couple of deadlines that led to impacts for downstream partners MIDE and CMODS. DETAILS: 1437056251a111375DESCRIPTION: New Submission1437056618a111375As Per Kevin :   This is a side effect of the physical storage changes that were made to the COM_DOC_NOTIFS schema under PRB000022539281 (which was a response to PRB000022533464)in June.  There is now only one non-interval partitioned segment on tables ACT  DOCVERSION  GENERIC  LNK  REQ  and REQ_DOC.  The drop partition job is passed a parameter telling whether to look at interval or non-interval partitioned segments.  The drop partition job avoids dropping what it sees as the only partition left and returns this error.  We can discuss the options at the morning meeting.  Options at this point: 1. DETAILS: 1438955417u414337DESCRIPTION: New Submission1438955617u414337Prachi and I have found an issue with what at first appeared to be duplicate rows in the fee_cls_cost_itm table in COM. Prachi found a number of instances where there were two rows for the same fee code. This caused a VCS issue  and will definitely cause a RESPA/TILA issue...as soon as CMIE come across it their code will fail.  On closer inspection the issue is not duplicate fee rows  it is that one row is for the valid current_applied_scenario_id and one is for a previous scenario_ID. I am not sure if the issue is the same as the one we had a few months back where the deltas are applied during the day but deletes are done at 5 am. I don't think it is since the issue there was that CORE had deleted the record. Here the issue is that MODE should have deleted the row when the product_request record changed and the row was no longer valid.  Here is SQL to find the current product_request_record for one of the loans: select product_request_ID from src_core2_deal.product_request join src_core2_deal.deal on deal.deal_id=product_request.deal_id where servicing_loan_acct_num=0423759927 and current_applied_scenario_id=scenario_id  This returns product_request_id 1028552318  In the fee_closing_cost table  for fee code 0855  we have two rows for that loan select *  from COM_ORIG_LOANS.FEE_CLS_COST_ITM  where srvcg_ln_acct_num= 0423759927  and fee_sor_cd=0855 and mode_soft_Del_ind is null  Loan number MODE_SURR_KY Fee 0423759927 1028201825 0855 Tax Service 0423759927 1041998079 0855 Tax Service  The MODE_SURR_KY is CLOSING_COST_ID in SRC. As you can see  when we check the SRC CLOSING_COST table  the product_request_id for the first one is 1028552317 not 1028552318. When the valid product_request_row changed  MODE should have removed the old row.  select * from src_core2_deal.closing_cost where closing_cost_id in (1028201825 1041998079)  MODE_SURR_KY PRODUCT_REQUEST_ID 1028201825  1028552317 1041998079  1028552318  Not sure how we handle issues that we find  problem ticket or is an email enough to start prod support on a Jira and research? This one needs to be address soon since it will cause downstream problems. S2C Delta for the this subject area - fee_cls_cost_itm identifies the soft deletes based on the mode soft delete indicator received from the SRC_CORE2_DEAL tables.
